<h3>1.3.4 Update Employee</h3>
<p><span class="badge badge-put">PUT</span> <code>/api/masters/employee/:code</code></p>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Updates an existing employee's details (excluding code). Validates existence, ensures name uniqueness against other records, and verifies designation/department foreign keys.</p>

<h3>Database Queries Executed:</h3>

<h4>Query 1: Existence Check</h4>
<pre>SELECT "C_EmpCode" FROM "Tbl_Emp_Mst" WHERE "C_EmpCode" = $1 AND "N_Deleted" = 0;</pre>

<div class="explanation-box">
    <div class="explanation-title">💡 Human Explanation of the Query:</div>
    Verifies that the target employee profile exists and is active before modifications.
</div>

<h4>Query 2: Uniqueness Check (Excluding Self)</h4>
<pre>SELECT "C_EmpCode" FROM "Tbl_Emp_Mst" WHERE LOWER("C_Name") = LOWER($1) AND "N_Deleted" = 0 AND "C_EmpCode" != $2;</pre>

<div class="explanation-box">
    <div class="explanation-title">💡 Human Explanation of the Query:</div>
    Prevents renaming an employee to match another active employee's name.
</div>

<h4>Query 3: Update Employee Profile</h4>
<pre>UPDATE "Tbl_Emp_Mst"
SET "C_NAMEPREFIX" = $1, "C_Name" = $2, "C_Grade" = $3, "C_Qualification" = $4,
    "C_Add_1" = $5, "C_Add_2" = $6, "C_Add_3" = $7, "C_Add_4" = $8, "C_Pin" = $9,
    "C_Mobile_No" = $10, "C_OFFICE_PHONE_NO" = $11, "C_OFFICE_PHONE_EXTNNO" = $12, "C_Fax" = $13, "C_Desc" = $14, "C_SEX" = $15,
    "D_DOB" = $16, "D_DOJ" = $17, "D_CONF_DATE" = $18, "D_DOW" = $19, "C_EMAIL_OFFICE" = $20, "C_EMAIL_PERSONAL" = $21,
    "C_Desig" = $22, "c_bankcode" = $23, "C_Accno" = $24, "d_modified" = NOW(), "c_modifier" = $25,
    "C_DEPT_CODE" = $26, "C_LOC_CODE" = $27, "D_RELIEVE_DATE" = $28, "C_ROLE" = $29, "C_JobDesc" = $30,
    "C_Hq_Address" = $31, "C_PAdd_1" = $32, "C_PAdd_2" = $33, "C_PAdd_3" = $34, "C_PAdd_4" = $35,
    "C_MAdd_1" = $36, "C_MAdd_2" = $37, "C_MAdd_3" = $38, "C_MAdd_4" = $39,
    "c_branch_name" = $40, "c_rtgs_neft" = $41, "c_hq_pin" = $42, "c_padd_pin" = $43, "c_madd_pin" = $44,
    "c_emp_type" = $45, "c_pan" = $46, "c_auto_report_email" = $47, "Aadhar_No" = $48, "C_ADHAR_NO" = $49,
    "C_ESI_NO" = $50, "C_EMERGENCYMOBILE_NO" = $51, "C_CONTACTNAME" = $52, "C_Parent" = $53
WHERE "C_EmpCode" = $54;</pre>

<div class="explanation-box">
    <div class="explanation-title">💡 Human Explanation of the Query:</div>
    Applies the updated details to the target employee record, updating <code>d_modified</code> and logging the administrator who updated it.
</div>

---

<h3>1.3.5 Delete Employee (Soft Delete)</h3>
<p><span class="badge badge-delete">DELETE</span> <code>/api/masters/employee/:code</code></p>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Soft-deletes an employee record, setting <code>N_Deleted = 1</code> to retain referential integrity.</p>

<h3>Database Queries Executed:</h3>
<pre>UPDATE "Tbl_Emp_Mst"
SET "N_Deleted" = 1, "d_modified" = NOW(), "c_modifier" = $1
WHERE "C_EmpCode" = $2;</pre>

<div class="explanation-box">
    <div class="explanation-title">💡 Human Explanation of the Query:</div>
    Performs a soft delete on the employee record by changing <code>N_Deleted</code> to <code>1</code>. This makes the employee inactive and hides them from active lists without corrupting transactional logs referencing this employee.
</div>


