<h1>🗺️ Part 3: FS Geography Masters</h1>
<p>Manages field force geographical territories, zones, regions, areas, sub areas, and sessions configuration.</p>

<h2>3.1 Zone Master</h2>
<p>The Zone Master manages primary geographical sales zones (e.g. <code>Z00001</code>, <code>Z00002</code>).</p>

<table style="width:100%">
    <tr>
        <th>Table Name</th>
        <th>Columns & Constraints</th>
        <th>Core Rules</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><code>Tbl_Zone_Mst</code></td>
        <td>
            <code>C_Code</code> VARCHAR(10) Primary Key (sequence format: <code>Z[0-9]+</code>)<br />
            <code>C_Name</code> VARCHAR(50) Not Null (Unique Name)<br />
            <code>C_Sh_Name</code> VARCHAR(7) Nullable<br />
            <code>n_deleted</code> SMALLINT Default 0 (Active)<br />
            <code>d_created</code> TIMESTAMP, <code>d_modified</code> TIMESTAMP, <code>c_modifier</code> VARCHAR(10)
        </td>
        <td>
            * Unique case-insensitive names<br />
            * Alphanumeric code sequence starts at <code>Z00001</code><br />
            * Soft delete via <code>n_deleted = 1</code>
        </td>
    </tr>
</table>

---

<h3>3.1.1 Get Next Zone Code</h3>
<p><span class="badge badge-get">GET</span> <code>/api/masters/zone/next-code</code></p>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Auto-calculates the next zone code sequence.</p>
<h3>Database Queries Executed:</h3>
<pre>SELECT "C_Code" FROM "Tbl_Zone_Mst"
WHERE "C_Code" ~ '^Z[0-9]+$'
ORDER BY CAST(SUBSTRING("C_Code" FROM 2) AS INTEGER) DESC
LIMIT 1;</pre>

---

<h3>3.1.2 Create Zone</h3>
<p><span class="badge badge-post">POST</span> <code>/api/masters/zone</code></p>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Creates a new zone. Enforces uniqueness check.</p>
<h3>Database Queries Executed:</h3>
<h4>Query 1: Uniqueness Check</h4>
<pre>SELECT "C_Code" FROM "Tbl_Zone_Mst" WHERE LOWER("C_Name") = LOWER($1) AND "n_deleted" = 0;</pre>
<h4>Query 2: Insert Zone</h4>
<pre>INSERT INTO "Tbl_Zone_Mst" ("C_Code", "C_Name", "C_Sh_Name", "n_deleted", "d_created", "c_modifier")
VALUES ($1, $2, $3, 0, NOW(), $4);</pre>

---

<h3>3.1.3 Get All / Search Zones</h3>
<p><span class="badge badge-get">GET</span> <code>/api/masters/zone</code></p>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Retrieves a paginated list of zones. Supports wildcard searches on code and name.</p>
<h3>Database Queries Executed:</h3>
<pre>SELECT "C_Code" as c_code, "C_Name" as c_name, "C_Sh_Name" as c_sh_name, "d_created", "d_modified", COUNT(*) OVER() as total_count
FROM "Tbl_Zone_Mst"
WHERE "n_deleted" = 0
  AND LOWER("C_Name") LIKE LOWER($1)
  AND LOWER("C_Code") LIKE LOWER($2)
ORDER BY "C_Code"
LIMIT $3 OFFSET $4;</pre>

---

<h3>3.1.4 Update Zone</h3>
<p><span class="badge badge-put">PUT</span> <code>/api/masters/zone/:code</code></p>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Updates an existing zone's name and short name. Enforces uniqueness excluding self.</p>
<h3>Database Queries Executed:</h3>
<h4>Query 1: Exists Check</h4>
<pre>SELECT "C_Code" FROM "Tbl_Zone_Mst" WHERE "C_Code" = $1 AND "n_deleted" = 0;</pre>
<h4>Query 2: Duplicate check excluding self</h4>
<pre>SELECT "C_Code" FROM "Tbl_Zone_Mst" WHERE LOWER("C_Name") = LOWER($1) AND "n_deleted" = 0 AND "C_Code" != $2;</pre>
<h4>Query 3: Update Zone fields</h4>
<pre>UPDATE "Tbl_Zone_Mst" SET "C_Name" = $1, "C_Sh_Name" = $2, "d_modified" = NOW(), "c_modifier" = $3 WHERE "C_Code" = $4;</pre>

---

<h3>3.1.5 Delete Zone (Soft Delete)</h3>
<p><span class="badge badge-delete">DELETE</span> <code>/api/masters/zone/:code</code></p>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Soft-deletes a zone record by setting <code>n_deleted = 1</code>.</p>
<h3>Database Queries Executed:</h3>
<pre>UPDATE "Tbl_Zone_Mst" SET "n_deleted" = 1, "d_modified" = NOW(), "c_modifier" = $1 WHERE "C_Code" = $2;</pre>


---

<h2>3.2 Region Master</h2>
<p>The Region Master manages geographical sales regions. Each region belongs to a specific Zone (e.g. <code>R0001</code>, <code>R0002</code>).</p>

<table style="width:100%">
    <tr>
        <th>Table Name</th>
        <th>Columns & Constraints</th>
        <th>Core Rules</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><code>Tbl_Region_Mst</code></td>
        <td>
            <code>C_Code</code> VARCHAR(10) Primary Key (sequence format: <code>R[0-9]+</code>)<br />
            <code>C_Name</code> VARCHAR(50) Not Null (Unique in same Zone)<br />
            <code>C_Sh_Name</code> VARCHAR(7) Nullable<br />
            <code>C_Zone_Code</code> VARCHAR(10) Not Null FK → <code>Tbl_Zone_Mst.C_Code</code><br />
            <code>n_lami</code> DOUBLE PRECISION Nullable (Latitude)<br />
            <code>n_lgmi</code> DOUBLE PRECISION Nullable (Longitude)<br />
            <code>n_deleted</code> SMALLINT Default 0 (Active)<br />
            <code>d_created</code> TIMESTAMP, <code>d_modified</code> TIMESTAMP, <code>c_modifier</code> VARCHAR(10)
        </td>
        <td>
            * Unique region name per Zone<br />
            * Alphanumeric code increments starting at <code>R0001</code><br />
            * Soft delete via <code>n_deleted = 1</code>
        </td>
    </tr>
</table>

---

<h3>3.2.1 Get Next Region Code</h3>
<p><span class="badge badge-get">GET</span> <code>/api/masters/region/next-code</code></p>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Auto-calculates the next region code sequence.</p>
<h3>Database Queries Executed:</h3>
<pre>SELECT "C_Code" FROM "Tbl_Region_Mst"
WHERE "C_Code" ~ '^R[0-9]+$'
ORDER BY CAST(SUBSTRING("C_Code" FROM 2) AS INTEGER) DESC
LIMIT 1;</pre>

---

<h3>3.2.2 Create Region</h3>
<p><span class="badge badge-post">POST</span> <code>/api/masters/region</code></p>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Creates a new region. Enforces Zone validation and name uniqueness within that Zone.</p>
<h3>Database Queries Executed:</h3>
<h4>Query 1: Validate Zone Exists</h4>
<pre>SELECT "C_Code" FROM "Tbl_Zone_Mst" WHERE "C_Code" = $1 AND "n_deleted" = 0 LIMIT 1;</pre>
<h4>Query 2: Uniqueness Check in same Zone</h4>
<pre>SELECT "C_Code" FROM "Tbl_Region_Mst" WHERE LOWER("C_Name") = LOWER($1) AND "C_Zone_Code" = $2 AND "n_deleted" = 0;</pre>
<h4>Query 3: Insert Region</h4>
<pre>INSERT INTO "Tbl_Region_Mst" ("C_Code", "C_Name", "C_Sh_Name", "C_Zone_Code", "n_lami", "n_lgmi", "n_deleted", "d_created", "c_modifier")
VALUES ($1, $2, $3, $4, $5, $6, 0, NOW(), $7);</pre>

---

<h3>3.2.3 Get All / Search Regions</h3>
<p><span class="badge badge-get">GET</span> <code>/api/masters/region</code></p>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Retrieves a paginated list of regions. Supports searching by region name, code, or zone name/code.</p>
<h3>Database Queries Executed:</h3>
<pre>SELECT r."C_Code" as c_code, r."C_Name" as c_name, r."C_Sh_Name" as c_sh_name, 
       r."C_Zone_Code" as c_zone_code, z."C_Name" as c_zone_name,
       r."n_lami", r."n_lgmi", r."d_created", r."d_modified", COUNT(*) OVER() as total_count
FROM "Tbl_Region_Mst" r
LEFT JOIN "Tbl_Zone_Mst" z ON r."C_Zone_Code" = z."C_Code"
WHERE r."n_deleted" = 0
  AND LOWER(r."C_Name") LIKE LOWER($1)
  AND LOWER(r."C_Code") LIKE LOWER($2)
  AND (LOWER(r."C_Zone_Code") LIKE LOWER($3) OR LOWER(z."C_Name") LIKE LOWER($3))
ORDER BY r."C_Code"
LIMIT $4 OFFSET $5;</pre>

---

<h3>3.2.4 Update Region</h3>
<p><span class="badge badge-put">PUT</span> <code>/api/masters/region/:code</code></p>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Updates an existing region. Enforces exist check, zone validation, and uniqueness excluding self.</p>
<h3>Database Queries Executed:</h3>
<h4>Query 1: Exists Check</h4>
<pre>SELECT "C_Code" FROM "Tbl_Region_Mst" WHERE "C_Code" = $1 AND "n_deleted" = 0;</pre>
<h4>Query 2: Validate Zone</h4>
<pre>SELECT "C_Code" FROM "Tbl_Zone_Mst" WHERE "C_Code" = $1 AND "n_deleted" = 0 LIMIT 1;</pre>
<h4>Query 3: Duplicate Name Check excluding self</h4>
<pre>SELECT "C_Code" FROM "Tbl_Region_Mst" WHERE LOWER("C_Name") = LOWER($1) AND "C_Zone_Code" = $2 AND "n_deleted" = 0 AND "C_Code" != $3;</pre>
<h4>Query 4: Update Queries</h4>
<pre>UPDATE "Tbl_Region_Mst"
SET "C_Name" = $1, "C_Sh_Name" = $2, "C_Zone_Code" = $3, "n_lami" = $4, "n_lgmi" = $5, "d_modified" = NOW(), "c_modifier" = $6
WHERE "C_Code" = $7;</pre>

---

<h3>3.2.5 Delete Region (Soft Delete)</h3>
<p><span class="badge badge-delete">DELETE</span> <code>/api/masters/region/:code</code></p>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Soft-deletes a region by setting <code>n_deleted = 1</code>.</p>
<h3>Database Queries Executed:</h3>
<pre>UPDATE "Tbl_Region_Mst" SET "n_deleted" = 1, "d_modified" = NOW(), "c_modifier" = $1 WHERE "C_Code" = $2;</pre>


