<h2>3.4 Sub Area Master</h3>
<p>The Sub Area Master manages sub-locality or sector information within areas. It uses a structured alphanumeric code system (e.g. <code>SA0001</code>, <code>SA0002</code>).</p>

<table style="width:100%">
    <tr>
        <th>Table Name</th>
        <th>Columns & Constraints</th>
        <th>Core Rules</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><code>Tbl_Sub_Area_Mst</code></td>
        <td>
            <code>C_Code</code> VARCHAR(10) Primary Key<br />
            <code>C_Name</code> VARCHAR(50) Not Null (Unique Name in same Area)<br />
            <code>C_Sh_Name</code> VARCHAR(7) Nullable<br />
            <code>C_Area_Code</code> VARCHAR(10) Not Null FK → <code>Tbl_Area_Mst.C_Code</code><br />
            <code>N_HQ_Flag</code> NUMERIC Default 0 (Same HQ Checkbox)<br />
            <code>n_deleted</code> SMALLINT Default 0 (Active)<br />
            <code>d_created</code> TIMESTAMP, <code>d_modified</code> TIMESTAMP, <code>c_modifier</code> VARCHAR(10)<br />
            <code>n_lami</code> VARCHAR(100) Nullable (Latitude)<br />
            <code>n_lgmi</code> VARCHAR(100) Nullable (Longitude)<br />
            <code>C_Classification_Code</code> VARCHAR(20) Nullable
        </td>
        <td>
            * Unique sub area name per Area<br />
            * Code format: <code>SA[0-9]+</code><br />
            * Validates parent Area Code exists<br />
            * Soft delete via <code>n_deleted = 1</code>
        </td>
    </tr>
</table>

---

<h3>3.4.1 Get Next Sub Area Code</h3>
<p><span class="badge badge-get">GET</span> <code>/api/masters/sub-area/next-code</code></p>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Auto-calculates the next sub area code in the sequence (e.g. if the highest code is <code>SA0041</code>, it suggests <code>SA0042</code>).</p>

<h3>Database Queries Executed:</h3>
<pre>SELECT "C_Code" 
FROM "Tbl_Sub_Area_Mst"
WHERE "C_Code" ~ '^SA[0-9]+$'
ORDER BY CAST(SUBSTRING("C_Code" FROM 3) AS INTEGER) DESC
LIMIT 1;</pre>

<div class="explanation-box">
    <div class="explanation-title">💡 Human Explanation of the Query:</div>
    This query calculates the next numeric code in the database.
    <ol>
        <li>We filter for codes starting with "SA" and ending in digits using regex match.</li>
        <li>We strip the "SA" prefix using <code>SUBSTRING("C_Code" FROM 3)</code>.</li>
        <li>We cast the result to an integer and sort descending to find the highest number in the system, which is then incremented by 1 and padded to four digits.</li>
    </ol>
</div>

---

<h3>3.4.2 Create Sub Area</h3>
<p><span class="badge badge-post">POST</span> <code>/api/masters/sub-area</code></p>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Creates a new sub area. Enforces name uniqueness within the same Area and validates that the parent Area exists.</p>

<h3>Database Queries Executed:</h3>

<h4>Query 1: Name Duplicate Check within the Same Area</h4>
<pre>SELECT "C_Code" 
FROM "Tbl_Sub_Area_Mst"
WHERE LOWER("C_Name") = LOWER($1)
  AND "C_Area_Code" = $2
  AND "n_deleted" = 0;</pre>

<h4>Query 2: Parent Area Validation</h4>
<pre>SELECT "C_Code" 
FROM "Tbl_Area_Mst" 
WHERE "C_Code" = $1 AND "n_deleted" = 0
LIMIT 1;</pre>

<h4>Query 3: Insert Sub Area</h4>
<pre>INSERT INTO "Tbl_Sub_Area_Mst" (
  "C_Code", 
  "C_Name", 
  "C_Sh_Name", 
  "C_Area_Code", 
  "N_HQ_Flag", 
  "n_lami", 
  "n_lgmi", 
  "C_Classification_Code", 
  "n_deleted", 
  "d_created", 
  "c_modifier"
)
VALUES ($1, $2, $3, $4, $5, $6, $7, $8, 0, NOW(), $9);</pre>

---

<h3>3.4.3 Get All / Search Sub Areas</h3>
<p><span class="badge badge-get">GET</span> <code>/api/masters/sub-area</code></p>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Retrieves a paginated list of sub areas. Supports wildcards and filtering by sub_area_name, code, and area_name.</p>

<h3>Database Queries Executed:</h3>
<pre>SELECT sa."C_Code" as c_code, sa."C_Name" as c_name, sa."C_Sh_Name" as c_sh_name, 
       sa."C_Area_Code" as c_area_code, a."C_Name" as c_area_name,
       sa."N_HQ_Flag" as n_hq_flag, sa."n_lami" as n_lami, sa."n_lgmi" as n_lgmi,
       sa."C_Classification_Code" as c_classification_code,
       sa."d_created", sa."d_modified", COUNT(*) OVER() AS total_count
FROM "Tbl_Sub_Area_Mst" sa
LEFT JOIN "Tbl_Area_Mst" a ON sa."C_Area_Code" = a."C_Code"
WHERE sa."n_deleted" = 0
  AND LOWER(sa."C_Name") LIKE LOWER($1)
  AND LOWER(sa."C_Code") LIKE LOWER($2)
  AND (LOWER(sa."C_Area_Code") LIKE LOWER($3) OR LOWER(a."C_Name") LIKE LOWER($3))
ORDER BY sa."C_Code"
LIMIT $4 OFFSET $5;</pre>

